@erhuodaosi The edges.flist is only used when you are using an external library to create edges. If you wish to use Canny edge detector (the default) you won't be needing to generate corresponding edges and you leave those values blank.

@erhuodaosi The training stops because it reaches the maximum number of iterations defined in your config file. You can change the `MAX_ITERS` in your config file to a value larger than `2e6`.

@knazeri

Hi,

Thank you for your timely response!
Thank you very much!
But it needs to cost much time to train for   2e6 iterations.In the pervious two models，
it takes a long time to train the model rather than 15 minutes.Is there any wrong with the
model training?
 
I would appreciate if you could help me，thank you!

Thanks，

@erhuodaosi There's nothing wrong with your code. I believe you are using the pre-trained weights and continue training. The pre-trained weights provided here are for models trained up to `2e6` iterations. So if you wish to continue training you need to set `MAX_ITERS` to a larger value!
